  "description": "The (3,5) pentagram torus knot — five crossings, three strands completing five revolutions around the torus core. pqScale = 0.975 produces near-maximum asymmetric coupling with a complex spectral overtone structure unlike the standard (2,3) trefoil. Sine strands for mathematically pure coupling. High braid depth makes the five-fold structure audible as spectral beating at irregular intervals. WEAVE-III: the pentagram is a different instrument.",
